MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

96-473. Oliver v. State.

Licking County, No. 95CA73. Appellant has filed an untimely appeal of the court of appeals’ decision affirming the denial of his post-conviction petition. This appeal involves a civil, post-conviction matter and not an appeal of a felony ease to which the provisions for delayed appeal in S.Ct.Prac.R. II(2)(A)(4) apply. Therefore,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that the motion for delayed appeal be, and hereby is, stricken.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that, in that appellant failed to perfect an appeal pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. II(2)(A)(1), this case be, and hereby is, dismissed for lack of jurisdiction.
